\tab THE THREE LAWS OF ROBOTICS \par
\par
\tab 1. A robot may not injure a human being, or, through inaction, allow a human being to come to harm. \par
\tab 2. A robot must obey the orders given it by human beings except where such orders would conflict with the First Law. \par
\tab 3. A robot must protect its own existence as long as such protection does not conflict with the First or Second Law. \par
\par
